title: bulk RNA-seq M1283LRC
characteristics_ch1: patient: BCP-ALL pediatric__mouse id: NOD scid gamma__cell type: PDX cell__cell status: LRC
growth_protocol_ch1: human patient cells are grown as patient-derived xenograft cells in immunodeficient NOD scid gamma mice and re-isolated from bone marrow
extract_protocol_ch1: cDNA synthesis protocol: Cells were sorted into lysis buffer composed of 0.2 % Triton X-100 (Sigma) and 2 U/μl of RNAse Inhibitor (Life Technologies). ERCC spike-in controls (Life Technologies) were added to the cell lysis mix at 1:5,000 dilution. RNA was cleaned-up from the crude lysate with Agencourt RNAclean XP SPRI beads (Beckman-Coulter). cDNA was synthesized and pre-amplified from 5 μl of lysate according to the Smart-seq2 protocol (Picelli et al., 2013)__0.2-1 ng of pre-amplified cDNA was used as input for tagmentation by the Nextera XT Sample Preparation Kit (Illumina), where amplification was performed for 12-14 PCR cycles.__Cells were isolated from the murine bone marrow, enriched by a MACS step and sorted for the population of interest. All steps were performed at 4°C.
data_processing: Sequencing reads were demultiplexed from the Nextera (i5 and i7) indices using deML (Renaud 2014, Bioinformatics)__Demultiplexed reads were aligned to the human genome (hg19) and ERCC reference using NextGenMap (Sedlazeck et al., 2013)__Count data was generated from mapped reads using featureCounts (Liao et al., 2014) on ENSEMBL gene models (GRCh38.74)__Genome_build: hg19__Supplementary_files_format_and_content: [.txt] processed data files are text files with count data, where columns equal to samples and rows equal to genes

growth_protocol_ch1: human patient cells are grown as patient-derived xenograft cells in immunodeficient NOD scid gamma mice and re-isolated from bone marrow

Cell lysis, reverse transcription and pre-amplification of cDNA was done on-chip using the SMARTer Ultra Low RNA Kit for C1 (Clontech).__0.2-1 ng of pre-amplified cDNA was used as input for tagmentation by the Nextera XT Sample Preparation Kit (Illumina), where amplification was performed for 12-14 PCR cycles.__Cells were isolated from the murine bone marrow, enriched by a MACS step and sorted for the population of interest. All steps were performed at 4°C.
data_processing: Sequencing reads were demultiplexed from the Nextera (i5 and i7) indices using deML (Renaud 2014, Bioinformatics)__Demultiplexed reads were aligned to the human genome (hg19) and ERCC reference using NextGenMap (Sedlazeck et al., 2013)__Count data was generated from mapped reads using featureCounts (Liao et al., 2014) on ENSEMBL gene models (GRCh38.74)__Genome_build: hg19__Supplementary_files_format_and_content: [.txt] processed data files are text files with count data, where columns equal to samples and rows equal to genes

growth_protocol_ch1: human patient cells are grown as patient-derived xenograft cells in immunodeficient NOD scid gamma mice and re-isolated from bone marrow
extract_protocol_ch1: cDNA synthesis protocol: cells were loaded on the 10-17 μm mRNA-seq IFC (Fluidigm) with ERCC spike-in controls. Cell lysis, reverse transcription and pre-amplification of cDNA was done on-chip using the SMARTer Ultra Low RNA Kit for C1 (Clontech).__0.2-1 ng of pre-amplified cDNA was used as input for tagmentation by the Nextera XT Sample Preparation Kit (Illumina), where amplification was performed for 12-14 PCR cycles.__Cells were isolated from the murine bone marrow, enriched by a MACS step and sorted for the population of interest. All steps were performed at 4°C.
data_processing: Sequencing reads were demultiplexed from the Nextera (i5 and i7) indices using deML (Renaud 2014, Bioinformatics)__Demultiplexed reads were aligned to the human genome (hg19) and ERCC reference using NextGenMap (Sedlazeck et al., 2013)__Count data was generated from mapped reads using featureCounts (Liao et al., 2014) on ENSEMBL gene models (GRCh38.74)__Genome_build: hg19__Supplementary_files_format_and_content: [.txt] processed data files are text files with count data, where columns equal to samples and rows equal to genes

growth_protocol_ch1: human patient cells are grown as patient-derived xenograft cells in immunodeficient NOD scid gamma mice and re-isolated from bone marrow
extract_protocol_ch1: cDNA synthesis protocol: cells were loaded on the 10-17 μm mRNA-seq IFC (Fluidigm) with ERCC spike-in controls. Cell lysis, reverse transcription and pre-amplification of cDNA was done on-chip using the SMARTer Ultra Low RNA Kit for C1 (Clontech).__0.2-1 ng of pre-amplified cDNA was used as input for tagmentation by the Nextera XT Sample Preparation Kit (Illumina), where amplification was performed for 12-14 PCR cycles.__Cells were isolated from the murine bone marrow, enriched by a MACS step and sorted for the population of interest. All steps were performed at 4°C.
data_processing: Sequencing reads were demultiplexed from the Nextera (i5 and i7) indices using deML (Renaud 2014, Bioinformatics)__Demultiplexed reads were aligned to the human genome (hg19) and ERCC reference using NextGenMap (Sedlazeck et al., 2013)__Count data was generated from mapped reads using featureCounts (Liao et al., 2014) on ENSEMBL gene models (GRCh38.74)__Genome_build: hg19__Supplementary_files_format_and_content: [.txt] processed data files are text files with count data, where columns equal to samples and rows equal to genes

data_processing: Sequencing reads were demultiplexed from the Nextera (i5 and i7) indices using deML (Renaud 2014, Bioinformatics)__Demultiplexed reads were aligned to the human genome (hg19) and ERCC reference usingSTAR (Dobin et al., 2014)__Count data was generated from mapped readson ENSEMBL gene models (GRCh38.74) considering UMI information using the Drop-seq pipeline (Macosko et al., 2015)__Genome_build: hg19__Supplementary_files_format_and_content: processed data files are text files with count data, where columns equal to samples and rows equal to genes
